cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with video-based person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a deep learning approach to learn view-invariant representations with access to limited labeled training samples, which involves training a model adversarially. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), as adversarial training is a popular technique in deep learning. The paper also mentions the need for flexible models to capture the dynamics in time-series observations, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on three benchmark datasets, indicating that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) as well. Finally, the paper deals with person re-identification, which involves privacy and security concerns, making it relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
